            <ul id="coach-list">
                <li><h4>Ken Barkey</h4></li>
                <li class="odd">
                    <h4 class="bio">Jerry Bernard</h4>
                <p>I am a teacher at the daVinci Institute in Jackson, MI were I mostly work with the alternative education program. It is quite a challenge but I'm all about positively influencing today's youth to move toward Jesus Christ - both at work and Crossroads Farm. I also love my Rottweiler puppy Ruby, hunting, and construction. I'm serving at CRF together with my wife. We are in our 4th year.</p></li>
                <li><h4 class="bio">Andrea Bernard</h4>
                <p> I enjoy working with youth and families in Hillsdale county. I do this through my job as a social worker and through the ministry of Crossroads Farm. My favorite part is investing in the lives of students. However, I also really enjoy listening to Doug speak and the encouragement of working with a team of people who really love Jesus and live it out in their daily lives. One of my favorite fun moments as a staff member was taking students on the white water rafting adventure, especially when we went down the natural waterslide.</p></li>
                <li class="odd">
                    <h4 class="bio">Richard Carpenter</h4>
                    <p>Dear Potential Fans,<br/> 
                    In order to be good fans you first need some stalking information.  My name is Rich, I'm 29, and my birthday is April 21, 1979.  I love photography and would like it to be part of my full time job/ministry when I grow up.  I've been with Crossroads Farm for almost nine years now and have seen God do things in students' lives that make it worth every bit and more of the time, lack of sleep, energy, money and other sacrifices that it takes to reach a student for Christ.</p>
                </li>
                <li><h4>Jackie Dishon</h4></li>
                <li class="odd">
                    <h4 class="bio">Rodney Forrister</h4>
                    <p>My name is Rod (Rodney) and this is my first year volunteering at CRF. I am the Youth Pastor at New Hope Chruch in Camden and as a church we decided that our youth group would start coming to CRF to experience more in the realm of having a group larger than 5 people. The resources that CRF has out weighs what I can do at New Hope strictly because of the numbers. CRF has two or three times the staff than our entire church and because they have been actively doing Youth Ministry for  almost 10 years here, the experience can do nothing but make each student have a more rounded middle school and high school experience. Whether it is the games that we play at CRF, or the trips we take with CRF, God is always at the center of it all.</p>
                </li>
                <li><h4>Grace Gardner</h4></li>
                <li class="odd"><h4>Sarah Gillary</h4></li>
                <li><h4>Andy Gollnick</h4></li>
                <li class="odd"><h4>Greg Hill</h4></li>
                <li>
                    <h4 class="bio">Betsy Hill</h4>
                    <p>To me, Crossroads is very special. I attended Crossroads as a student in High School and now I have the opportunity to give back to this great organization by volunteering to work with Senior High girls. There are not many places in Hillsdale County where a teenager can go where he/ she will feel loved, accepted, and have the opportunity to accept Christ as his/ her personal Savior. Crossroads is where I met my husband and where we will serve (Lord willing) for the rest of our lives.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="odd"><h4>Virginia Holmes</h4></li>
                <li>
                    <h4 class="bio">Eric Joseph</h4>
                    <p>As a college student, I like to
                        hang out with people apart from my studies.  I love to sing and play
