                        cannot drive out darkness; only light can do that. Hate cannot drive out
                        hate; only love can do that," a  quote from Martin Luther King Jr.  As it
                        says in the Bible in one of the ten commandments: Love your neighbor. 
                        Always be the one that shows love to all, including your enemies.  Jesus
                        did it, why not us.  We are supposed to live like Jesus and He said to
                        show love and kindness.  I can preach a sermon on this specific topic and
                        someday I would love to.  I'm a big Jesus freak (which, there isn't
                        anything wrong with that) and I will always stick up for Christ.  I love
                        the Bible and I do my best to abide by it each day (even I have trouble
                        doing that and always will).</p>                
                </li>
